cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on secure sharing of identity attributes using attribute-based encryption. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes a decentralised architecture using a name system. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses storing and sharing user attributes. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper presents an implementation of the proposed architecture. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper addresses the issue of users reclaiming their digital identities, which has societal implications.
